column5: that was cool stuff!!!!
what a PIG, that's terrible table manners

Hey...my co-workers father's best buddy's cousin's barber caught that pike in a remote lake in Manitoba...it was HUGE....anyone want me to post a pic...even snapped a photo of the pike with the fish in it's mouth!!
looks like a tiger to me.
I came upon this.. .. pretty neat... circle of life stuff...
Jeez, I think he was eating with thoughts of voracious appetite rather than using a ruler to see if it would fit. Looks like he was trying to ram it in.
EH!!   pas mal cool..

Pike eating a brown trout. Very cool, kinda reminds me of river X. I was told some people kill any pike they catch there due to the number of brown they eat. Not a good thing to kill them...  I guess that was not taken in Canada is it? England?
Oh, not that old video again  Seen that last year TJ, but its still cool. Some people were arguing whether it was a pike or a musky.  Joey
Mets-en!!  ahaah  cheers TJ
It's a musky..but I think we need a confirmation from Simcoe Peter.
Sorry, I vote pike!  No hard feelings I hope! Since I'm right!  <joke btw>
Hey, we're sensitive and that is just wrong.  Ha, just kidding  Awesome video. Nature, it's so amazing.
Lol, thats what I thought too!
definite pike
Looks like a Tiger Muskie to me.. anywho.. whatever it is, it clearly bit off a bit more then it could chew..
Pig, all them smaller bait fish around! It might have choked on that one!
haha that's crazy! silly fish being greedy.
scan through the other videos under that one and watch the one of a pike attacking a guy releasing a fish.
absolutely no doubt about it 100% positively a tiger musky
Yup muskie... i was watching the poor trout... lol
Ya i saw thet last week on Youtube i was trying to show my kids what a pike looked like LOL I had one of those attached to my walleye once LOL
Muskie, Tiger Muskie, Pike....  I like to call it "Big fish eat little fish"  There...someone disagree with me....LOL

A young Tiger muskie based on the markings. all the pike I've seen don't have the verticle bars that are so clear in the vid. poor brown trout, I don't think that fish was going to fit entirely in that muskie.
COOL VIDEO CLIP TJ..  ...mother nature at her finest !!!!! survival of the fittes,eat or be eaten....cheers
Not to often you see a 40 lb pike eating a 12 lb brook trout
Note to self.  Never put hands, feet, or other body parts near water again.  Always use a net!!!  Those were some pretty cool vids.  Thanks for sharing.
I wonder if that muskie survived after that... Won't be surprised if the trout got stuck.
